e ABG in this group was reduced from 17.6 dB to 8.7 dB in the post-operative period. Post-operative tympano- gram showed that approximately 90% cases had a type-A curve followed by type-C (5%) and type-B curve (5%) (<xref ref-type="table" rid="T5">Table.5</xref>). Statistical comparison of the two groups showed a statistically significant difference (P=0.010).</p><table-wrap id="T5" position="float"><label>Table 5</label><caption><p>Pre and post-operative tympanogram in Group B</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th style="background-color:#D9D9D9;" align="left" rowspan="2" colspan="1">
